abstract: Two Carnival Corp cruise ships collided on Friday in the port of Mexico's Caribbean resort of Cozumel, the luxury cruise operator said, crushing the stern of a 952-foot-long (290-meter) vessel and leaving passengers stunned at the loud impact.
snippet: Two Carnival Corp cruise ships collided on Friday in the port of Mexico's Caribbean resort of Cozumel, the luxury cruise operator said, crushing the stern of a 952-foot-long (290-meter) vessel and leaving passengers stunned at the loud impact.
lead_paragraph: MEXICO CITY — Two Carnival Corp cruise ships collided on Friday in the port of Mexico's Caribbean resort of Cozumel, the luxury cruise operator said, crushing the stern of a 952-foot-long (290-meter) vessel and leaving passengers stunned at the loud impact.
headline_main: 'Oh My God, Look at That Ship!': Massive Cruise Liners Collide Off Mexico
headline_print_headline: 'Oh My God, Look at That Ship!': Massive Cruise Liners Collide Off Mexico

abstract: Researchers said the profiles, linked to the Epoch Media Group, used photos generated by artificial intelligence in a preview of an “eerie, tech-enabled future of disinformation.”
snippet: Researchers said the profiles, linked to the Epoch Media Group, used photos generated by artificial intelligence in a preview of an “eerie, tech-enabled future of disinformation.”
lead_paragraph: Facebook said on Friday that it had removed hundreds of accounts with ties to the Epoch Media Group, parent company of the Falun Gong-related publication and conservative news outlet The Epoch Times.

abstract: We loved it! We hated it! We were mixed! Here’s how we reviewed each chapter in the main saga. Some were even Critic’s Picks.
snippet: We loved it! We hated it! We were mixed! Here’s how we reviewed each chapter in the main saga. Some were even Critic’s Picks.
lead_paragraph: The critics’ consensus on “The Rise of Skywalker,” the final installment of “Star Wars,” is… not great. According to Rotten Tomatoes, before the movie opened, it stood at 57 percent fresh.
